perator that removes $k_0$ number of particles from $m$ fermion\nsystem. Numerical results obtained using the exact formulas for two-body\n($k=2$) Hamiltonians (in some examples for $k=3,4$) and the asymptotic formulas\nclearly establish that in general the smoothed form of the bivariate transition\nstrength densities take bivariate Gaussian form for isolated finite quantum\nsystems. Extensions of these results to bosonic systems and EGUE ensembles with\nfurther symmetries are discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Apr 2015 07:21:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-04-06"}
